CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 21, 1941, pg. 8 reads: "Prominent Philadelphians Guests Of Pittsburghers - A pleasing note to the week-end was the visit of Atty. and Mrs. Herbert Millen of Philadelphia to the Wilbur Douglasses of Dean Street. They were breakfast guests of the Ira F. Lewises Sunday morning when this charming picture was taken.  Left to right: Atty. Wilbur Douglass, Mrs. Gertrude McKenzie, Mrs. Wilbur Douglass, Mrs. Robert L. Vann, Mrs. Herbert Millen, Mrs. Ira F. Lewis, Mr. Lewis and Atty. Millen. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait from left: Atty. Wilbur Douglass, Gertrude McKenzie, Mrs. Wilbur Douglass, Jessie Vann, Mrs. Herbert Millen, Harriet Lewis, Ira F. Lewis and Atty. Millen, in backyard garden of Ira Lewis residence, 616 Wilkinsburg Avenue, Homewood
